Python server with flash, client html
1. Install Flask and Flask-SocketIO by running pip install Flask Flask-SocketIO in your terminal.
2. Save the server-side code in a file (e.g., server.py) and the client-side code in an HTML file (e.g., index.html).
3. Run the server using python server.py in one terminal window.
4. Open the HTML file in a web browser.
